    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="149"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1601</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Greek Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RG1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Roussos</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Aide-Mémoire</hi>
                </p>
                <p>By order of my Government I have the honor to inform you that the chief of
                    Bulgarian propaganda at Berne … called at the Greek Royal Legation at Berne to
                    propose an understanding between Greece and Bulgaria, the result of which would
                    be withdrawal from the Macedonian front.</p>
                <p>He offered the explanation that Bulgaria, surrounded by enemies and fearing
                    subjection to Germany, is seeking friendly support in the Balkans.</p>
                <p>The Royal Government in bringing the foregoing to Your Excellency’s knowledge
                    wishes to declare that Greece will not listen to proposals of a separate
                    understanding with any of our enemies.<note n="3" xml:id="d149fn3">Acknowledged
                        Apr. 26, with the observation that “The Secretary of State notes, with
                        pleasure, the concluding statement …”</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
